Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgyXcBbYI5UvzNHWpud4AaABAg.AM1vhYUXWaZAM8Owh7wm8g,UgyXcBbYI5UvzNHWpud4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi @96Caleb96, You can download Apple and Google Maps, but they're not always ideal for navigating the medinas in Morocco. We found some parts of the medinas incorrectly mapped, especially because of earthquakes, which changed some of the routes that Apple and Google haven't updated, unfortunately. —Judy",2025-08-22T20:09:39Z,2025-08-22T20:09:39Z,1,True,,2026-05-13T02:01:41.575971
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgyXcBbYI5UvzNHWpud4AaABAg.AM1vhYUXWaZAM8SRBCFxcw,UgyXcBbYI5UvzNHWpud4AaABAg,@96Caleb96,"​​@FindingGinaMarieThankyou very much! Atleast i know not to fully rely on it, will try and use landmarks and comms instead!",2025-08-22T20:40:09Z,2025-08-22T21:14:27Z,0,True,,2026-05-13T02:01:41.575989
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgyXcBbYI5UvzNHWpud4AaABAg.AM1vhYUXWaZAM8WTfayjJm,UgyXcBbYI5UvzNHWpud4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Yes, paying close attention to landmarks helps a lot, and we tried to use the same paths as often as we could. It's challenging when you want to explore, because you can go deep and find yourself in a maze where everything starts to look the same! Some people suggest having a walking tour to help you navigate, but we seemed to figure it out okay on our own. By the time we did a walking tour, we had become pretty comfortable navigating it on our own. —Judy",2025-08-22T21:15:27Z,2025-08-22T21:15:27Z,1,True,,2026-05-13T02:01:41.575994
