Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgygYPhcCHOGoIbCWT14AaABAg.AEsOPMUEOXWAEubupeRRgI,UgygYPhcCHOGoIbCWT14AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,This may be the restaurant that you are referring to in Marrakech. It's where we had breakfast several of the days that we visited (but they also serve other meals as well): https://www.mandalasociety.co/marrakech. —Judy,2025-02-24T02:43:21Z,2025-02-24T02:43:21Z,1,True,,2026-05-13T02:01:45.331405
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgyTkvvc5TMDaXXsxAR4AaABAg.AEro9JX76GPAErpYzBMHFL,UgyTkvvc5TMDaXXsxAR4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Donah, Hmmm. It's tricky. El Badi Palace was pretty cool. We enjoyed it a lot. We have heard from some of our viewers that they really liked the Berber Museum and Majorelle Garden, too. I think it mostly depends on what type of experience you are interested in. I've heard that the garden is one of the most photographed and well-known gardens in Morocco. If you're into fashion, perhaps knowing that the garden was once owned by fashion designer Yves Saint Laurent will tip the scale for you. We are more interested in the deeper history and architecture, which is why we prioritized El Badi Palace. Thanks so much for watching. We have a full series from Morocco that might be interesting to you. We really enjoyed our 40+ days there. We don't think you will go wrong with either site, but they are very different! —Judy
