Tourism,wFZyNQAIcdE,UgwYwFYnszJcBUX6D114AaABAg,,@jaxwhiteley6743,"I've visited many of these places and  I enjoyed them. Not pushy vendors, I avoid those, and I'm not gullible. I think the trick is going off season and managing expectations. Like go to Venice in spring or fall. There is more than a gondola and Rialto Bridge.  There is the Doge Palace, San Marco Cathedral and just walking around finding treasures of art, fountains, statues down the various alleys.  You've haven't experienced Venice if you haven't got lost!  I lived in Hawaii for almost a decade, morning hike up diamond head for sunrise, hike the falls behind UH in Manoa Valley, go to the Pali, go to Northshore!  People are stupid if they don't get out of Waikiki.",2026-05-10T18:14:10Z,2026-05-10T18:29:30Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-13T02:02:30.421027
