Tourism,wFZyNQAIcdE,Ugz6X-COb0R2PG7IGrV4AaABAg,,@raucousmortuary,"It was disappointing to see so much misinformation about both sides of Niagara Falls. Yes, the Canada side is touristy. But it also has world-class views, many different amazing experiences (Cave of the Winds, Maid of the Mist, The Tunnel) to see the Falls up close, which is exciting as hell no matter how many others are there. Also, southern Ontario has great rural spaces including wineries, scenic gorges, and Niagara-on-the-Lake, a gorgeous region. The US side most certainly does NOT ""have only one observation deck"". There is one TOWER, but multiple ways to view the falls in a more natural setting than Canada including their own Cave of the Winds and Maid of the Mist. There are also many other attractions in the area"" Whirlpool Park, Devil's Hole with its spectacular and challenging hikes, Fort Niagara, Power Vista, and the Aquarium. This video is full of it. Totally worth visiting especially in September when the crowds leave but everything is still open.",2026-05-09T15:20:13Z,2026-05-09T15:20:39Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-13T02:02:30.421074
