Tourisme,tQG5jBBGn2Q,UgzMXF6D3DQO4fEYqFt4AaABAg,,@schweinhund7966,"After spending 6 months in a tent in Central America with the US Army, I took a 35 day vacation to South Africa; Zimbabwe and Botswana in 1985.  I drove solo from Johannesburg, Pretoria, Phalaborwa; Graskop; Pilgrim’s Rest; kruger National Park; Carolina; Royal Natal National Park; Rorke’s Drift; Islandlwana; And Durban; flew to Port Elizabeth and drove to Oudtshoorn, Cape Agulhas and Cape Town for a total of 4K kilometers (manual transmission and NO GPS) over 28 days.  It was an incredible safe, comfortable and eye-opening “adventure.”  I flew on to Zimbabwe and Botswana before heading to Asia for my next assignment.  I returned to South Africa in 2015 and could see the obvious deterioration!  Apartheid was stupid but what has replaced it is blatant corruption and serious decline.  I can only imagine what Rhodesia was like.",2026-05-11T18:21:08Z,2026-05-11T18:21:08Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-13T02:03:52.569716
